article.headline: Wichita St. 94, Chicago St. 44
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- Ben Smith scored 22 points as Wichita State rolled to a 94-44 victory over Chicago State Wednesday night. Joe Ragland had 12 points and David Kyles added 10 for the Shockers (8-2), winners of six straight. They had no problem with Chicago State (0-10), shooting 50 percent in the first half on the way to a 53-24 lead. Wichita State outrebounded the Cougars 53-34 and limited them to 27 percent shooting. Twelve players scored for the Shockers, who finished with 44 percent accuracy from the field. Jeremy Robinson had 13 points and Lee Fisher scored 10 for Chicago State.
